instructions: Preheat oven to 375F and grease a 12-cup muffin tin with nonstick spray. Melt the butter in a medium skillet over medium heat. Whisk in 2 teaspoons cinnamon and granulated sugar and add apples, stirring to coat. Cook for 5-10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until apples are tender. Divide the batter evenly between the prepared muffin cups, using your fingertips to lightly smooth out the tops of the muffins as needed. Bake at 375F for 5 minutes, and then reduce heat to 350 and bake about another 15 minutes, until a toothpick inserted into the center of one comes out clean. Muffins are best kept in an airtight container at room temperature, but can be kept in the refrigerator for longer storage.

Cut off and discard 1 end of baguette, then cut 12 (1/4-inch-thick) crosswise slices from baguette (reserve remainder for another use).
